<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code> element contains one or more <a href="/docs/elements/native/tr/"><code>&lt;tr&gt;</code></a> elements that form the footer of a table. While it can appear after <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a> and before <a href="/docs/elements/native/tbody/"><code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code></a> in the HTML, browsers will render it at the bottom of the table.</p>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze styles tfoot cells with a raised background, bold text, and a thicker top border to visually distinguish summary rows from data rows.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Summary totals:</strong> Sum, average, or count of column values</li>
      <li><strong>Aggregate data:</strong> Calculated values derived from tbody data</li>
      <li><strong>Table conclusions:</strong> Final remarks or totals for financial/statistical tables</li>
      <li><strong>Repeated footers:</strong> Printed tables can repeat tfoot on each page</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not Needed</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Simple tables:</strong> Tables without summary data don't require tfoot</li>
      <li><strong>Navigation links:</strong> Pagination or table controls should be outside the table</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

